Dialogue: 0,1:20:39.60,1:20:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,manufactures data when there isn't any.\NThere's nothing going on. You sit on a
Dialogue: 0,1:20:43.92,1:20:49.12,Default,,0,0,0,,park bench and the bus is late today and\Nyou got nothing to do but sit and look
Dialogue: 0,1:20:49.12,1:20:54.23,Default,,0,0,0,,at the lawn.\NHow many people like to sit and watch
Dialogue: 0,1:20:54.23,1:21:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the grass grow? Huh? Hands.\NYou can see rather than sit and watch
Dialogue: 0,1:21:01.28,1:21:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the grass grow\Nthat the intellect, the mind, the ego is
Dialogue: 0,1:21:07.04,1:21:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,going to create a novelty and excitement\Nand something going on. It's going to
Dialogue: 0,1:21:13.52,1:21:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,create a false movie when there's really\Nno movie going on. All right? The mind
Dialogue: 0,1:21:21.36,1:21:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,thinks, the ego thinks if there's no\Nmovie going on, I will die. So, all
Dialogue: 0,1:21:26.48,1:21:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,right. What you have to surrender then\Nis the payoff. You experience it as
Dialogue: 0,1:21:32.56,1:21:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,interest however you experience it of\Nthe experiencer.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:38.00,1:21:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,What would happen if you didn't\Nexperience anything?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:44.88,1:21:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,What would happen if your capacity to\Nexperience just got unplugged?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:53.19,1:21:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Silence.\NInfinite, exquisite.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:59.52,1:22:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The source of the self got imminent.\NInfinite silence.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:06.40,1:22:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And the joy of one's existence is all\Nthat's left.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:11.92,1:22:18.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The joy of one's own existence\Nis completely and sufficiently
Dialogue: 0,1:22:18.23,1:22:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,self-fulfilling that it needs nothing.\NWhat do I need in a room to be happy?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:30.88,1:22:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Absence.\NWhat is that book? Less is more. Huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:56.23,1:23:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Less is more.\NOne reaches that state or there is no no
Dialogue: 0,1:23:03.44,1:23:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,need for anything, no desire for\Nanything.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:08.08,1:23:14.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is perfect in and of itself.\NEverything is exquisite.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:14.71,1:23:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The sacredness of all of creation shines\Nforth.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:18.96,1:23:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like it goes from black and white\Nto technicolor.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:22.96,1:23:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,There's like a everything has a radiance\Nemanating from it. What you think of as
Dialogue: 0,1:23:28.32,1:23:36.71,Default,,0,0,0,,a nonsensient tree is actually aware.\NIt radiates out the essence of its
Dialogue: 0,1:23:36.71,1:23:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,divinity as you walk by the field.\NActually the tree actually is aware of
Dialogue: 0,1:23:43.36,1:23:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,your passage. Yeah.\NThe sacredness of all existence then
Dialogue: 0,1:23:48.80,1:23:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,shines forth\Nso you won't be bored.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:55.44,1:24:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You give up experiencing.\NThe TV doesn't turn off. Instead
Dialogue: 0,1:24:03.67,1:24:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,it radiates forth\Nits exquisite beauty. Huh? Everything
Dialogue: 0,1:24:10.96,1:24:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,that is\Nin the way bows down and serves you as
Dialogue: 0,1:24:15.60,1:24:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,you walk up by it. Everything is aware\Nof your divinity.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:20.96,1:24:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is aware of your awareness of\Nyour divinity. And each thing
Dialogue: 0,1:24:27.36,1:24:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,in a way that's not explicable.\NMaybe in the realm of cartoons.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:35.36,1:24:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,In cartoons,\Nyou see the tree,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:40.88,1:24:48.63,Default,,0,0,0,,blinks its eyes and looks at you\Nin that state. Doesn't blink eyes. It
Dialogue: 0,1:24:48.63,1:24:56.71,Default,,0,0,0,,just radiates awareness that divinity is\Naware of divinity as divinity.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:56.71,1:25:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The sacredness of all that exists shines\Nforth. So instead of amusement, the
Dialogue: 0,1:25:02.88,1:25:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,amusement of the experiencer which is\Nonly passing superficial amusement,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:08.63,1:25:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,linear amusement\Nin its place shines forth
Dialogue: 0,1:25:14.88,1:25:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the incredible essence of divinity\Nitself.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:20.00,1:25:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, nothing is lost and all is\Ngained.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:26.80,1:25:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, that should take care of the\Nego's fears. See, because the ego fears
Dialogue: 0,1:25:32.56,1:25:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,if I let go dominance, if you uh\Nsurrender all desire and want, uhoh,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:39.60,1:25:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,all desire and want,\Nthose of you who have gone through the
Dialogue: 0,1:25:47.67,1:25:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,phase of renunciation and left the\Nworld, you remember you're sitting alone
Dialogue: 0,1:25:52.63,1:26:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,in a room and there's a chair and a\Nlittle table and a couch or bed.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:00.32,1:26:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,in a candle there and somebody says,\N"What do you want?"
Dialogue: 0,1:26:04.96,1:26:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, nothing.\NAnything you need?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:09.28,1:26:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,No,\Nyou don't need or want anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:12.63,1:26:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is complete and total as it\Nis. You say, "Well, if you don't eat,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:16.56,1:26:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,the body will fall over and you'll die."\NSo,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:21.67,1:26:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,so what about it?\NIt's not even interesting.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:28.88,1:26:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,is not even interesting.\NThe body goes on of its own because it's
Dialogue: 0,1:26:33.28,1:26:38.63,Default,,0,0,0,,a karmic windup toy is destined to\Ncertain things
Dialogue: 0,1:26:38.63,1:26:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and\NI think very often it you're fulfilling
Dialogue: 0,1:26:42.88,1:26:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,a contract that was made before you\Nreentered the body and of course when
Dialogue: 0,1:26:47.60,1:26:54.23,Default,,0,0,0,,you do you auto have automatic amnesia.\NThe minute you the spirit re-enters
Dialogue: 0,1:26:54.23,1:26:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,another embryo\Nuh you're disconnected amnesia sets in.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:59.36,1:27:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh but you can watch from the way your\Nlife goes that certain agreements and
Dialogue: 0,1:27:03.92,1:27:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,contracts must have been made because\Nwhen there's no desire to continue to
Dialogue: 0,1:27:08.80,1:27:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,walk or even breathe in and out, it goes\Non about his business and then you look
Dialogue: 0,1:27:13.44,1:27:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,at what was its business and you\Nconclude from after a number of years by
Dialogue: 0,1:27:18.15,1:27:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,seeing what was done. Oh, that must have\Nbeen the agreement. You don't know till
Dialogue: 0,1:27:22.48,1:27:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,it's completed that that's what it must\Nhave been. They say you're going to
Dialogue: 0,1:27:27.12,1:27:29.67,Default,,0,0,0,,write a book or you're going to give\Nlectures or you're going to share what
Dialogue: 0,1:27:29.67,1:27:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,you know uh because that's um your joy\Nto do so. You share what you know out of
Dialogue: 0,1:27:37.36,1:27:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the joy of your own existence out of the\Nthankfulness of divinity as the source
Dialogue: 0,1:27:41.52,1:27:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,of your\Num beingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:47.60,1:27:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So each each one of us does the best\Nthey can I think to share what we have
Dialogue: 0,1:27:53.76,1:27:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,become for the benefit of life itself.\NWe do it in relationship. We do it as
Dialogue: 0,1:27:59.12,1:28:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,parents. We do it as students. Without\Nthe students, what would the professor
Dialogue: 0,1:28:03.52,1:28:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,do? You know, so the student is serving\Nthe professor because without students,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:08.08,1:28:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,the professor wouldn't have a job. What\Ndo you
Dialogue: 0,1:28:11.12,1:28:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll say mediators. If it wasn't for me,\Nthere wouldn't be any cattle out there.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:18.15,1:28:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,200 million cattle wouldn't have\Nexistence. So you see everything serves
Dialogue: 0,1:28:22.40,1:28:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,everything else and to not see that is\Njust positionality
Dialogue: 0,1:28:27.67,1:28:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and uh\Nall right so
Dialogue: 0,1:28:31.76,1:28:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted to get to the essence then by\Ncritical factor analysis we look at a
Dialogue: 0,1:28:37.36,1:28:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,complex system and there's certainly\Nnothing more complex than the ego itself
Dialogue: 0,1:28:41.60,1:28:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,including all its content throughout all\Nthe time
Dialogue: 0,1:28:45.67,1:28:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,staggering we can calibrate its level of\Nconsciousness that gives is at least a
Dialogue: 0,1:28:51.36,1:28:56.08,Default,,0,0,0,,starting point we can say what is going\Non at that level of consciousness and
Dialogue: 0,1:28:56.08,1:28:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,how do we know that it's going on we\Nknow that that's going on because of the
Dialogue: 0,1:28:59.84,1:29:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,experiencer\Nall right so every experiencer aside
Dialogue: 0,1:29:03.76,1:29:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,from just experiencing has already been\Nprogrammed to selectivity it will select
Dialogue: 0,1:29:10.23,1:29:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,it will automatically select uh that\Nwhich is to be experienced that's our
Dialogue: 0,1:29:15.60,1:29:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,inheritance from the amoeba the amoeba\Nalready knows that there's no point of
Dialogue: 0,1:29:19.60,1:29:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,searching ing out a piece of steel. He's\Nalready got his nothing. And here he's
Dialogue: 0,1:29:22.88,1:29:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,got a nice little joy couple molecules\Nof protein that's worth looking at. So
Dialogue: 0,1:29:28.40,1:29:36.23,Default,,0,0,0,,already the experiencer is somewhat\Nselective due to prior programming
Dialogue: 0,1:29:36.23,1:29:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,with ordinary spiritual work\Ntranscending one thing after another
Dialogue: 0,1:29:40.00,1:29:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,that the programming of the of the\Nexperiencer is is changed.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:47.28,1:29:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The experiencer still until the final\Nstage persists. It what changes is what
Dialogue: 0,1:29:54.32,1:30:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,it's experiencing because now its\Npriorities have changed
Dialogue: 0,1:30:01.92,1:30:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,at the lowest level. It's only concerned\Nwith selfishness. At higher level now
Dialogue: 0,1:30:07.28,1:30:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,it's concerned with gratitude\Nbut it's still experiencing is it not?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:12.56,1:30:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,However, it's a lot more pleasant to\Nexperience up here than it is down
Dialogue: 0,1:30:16.15,1:30:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,there. You know what I mean?\NI'd rather be on top of the horse and
Dialogue: 0,1:30:19.92,1:30:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,under the horse. You know what I mean?\NIf I got my brothers, I'll be the rider
Dialogue: 0,1:30:26.32,1:30:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and not the victim. You know what I'm\Nsaying?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:29.76,1:30:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. So,\Nthe transformation of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:30:35.60,1:30:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,which goes on as you evolve spiritually\Nmakes the work actually easier and
Dialogue: 0,1:30:39.67,1:30:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,easier. It actually becomes easier. It\Nbecomes your nature. Becomes your
Dialogue: 0,1:30:45.28,1:30:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,nature. If you see anything that's less\Nthan perfect already, there's a little
Dialogue: 0,1:30:50.15,1:30:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,bill in the back of your nose. It must\Nbe back of your head. I mean, I was
Dialogue: 0,1:30:54.15,1:31:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,going to say see how it smells, how it\Nlooks or what you think about it. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:02.00,1:31:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Which brings up that all experiencing\Nthen uh is processed through a modality.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:08.80,1:31:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So the experiencer\Nlives off the juice of experiencing
Dialogue: 0,1:31:14.32,1:31:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,motivated by curiosity\Nand experiences it via via various
Dialogue: 0,1:31:20.40,1:31:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,modalities various modalities.\NThe more evolved you become uh the more
Dialogue: 0,1:31:26.80,1:31:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,refined you might say the modality\Nuh the less it's negativity the less
Dialogue: 0,1:31:31.44,1:31:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,it's pain. As life becomes more and more\Npleasant, a lot of the motivation to get
Dialogue: 0,1:31:36.88,1:31:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual in the first place is gone.\NLife's pretty good now. So, the fires of
Dialogue: 0,1:31:45.36,1:31:52.71,Default,,0,0,0,,hell have stopped burning around your\Nfeet.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:52.71,1:31:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,When you're in the throws of addiction,\Nboy, are you ever willing to surrender
Dialogue: 0,1:31:56.48,1:32:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,everything to God and do the 12step\Nprogram. But now that you got a good job
Dialogue: 0,1:32:00.71,1:32:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're happily married again and a\Nnew car, uh it's somehow less pressure
Dialogue: 0,1:32:06.48,1:32:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,to surrender things and let them go to\NGod. And
Dialogue: 0,1:32:12.15,1:32:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,so life in the higher levels of\Nconsciousness can also stall people out.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:19.28,1:32:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we said that\Nby calibration we find that only 4% of
Dialogue: 0,1:32:25.92,1:32:32.71,Default,,0,0,0,,the world's human population ever\Nreaches level 500. 4%.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:32.71,1:32:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at all that stuff about love out\Nthere. 4%
Dialogue: 0,1:32:36.88,1:32:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,ever really get there. Everybody has a\Nfantasy about love. They're talking
Dialogue: 0,1:32:40.88,1:32:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,about addictions, the glamour of it,\Npossessiveness.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:46.88,1:32:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,only 4% ever reach level 500. 500 is the\Nbeginning of the spiritual domain. It's
Dialogue: 0,1:32:54.00,1:33:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,a different paradigm. It's the paradigm\Nuh that reality is primarily subjective.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:02.32,1:33:08.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Although the objective linearity is\Nthere, it's the subjective experiencing
Dialogue: 0,1:33:08.23,1:33:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,of it. I mean, what good is a formula if\Nthere's no way to look at the formula?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:13.67,1:33:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So the objective world in and of itself\Nis useless.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:18.08,1:33:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The universe doesn't need you. Nothing\Nis added or subtracted by your being
Dialogue: 0,1:33:22.15,1:33:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,here. The objective universe doesn't\Nneed you at all. Nor does it need to be
Dialogue: 0,1:33:26.23,1:33:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,appreciated. It's just fine in and of\Nitself.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:29.60,1:33:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Subjectivity then is the introduction of\Na different paradigm.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:34.32,1:33:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the basis of the sense of I. I.\NSo when you come to the last door,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:42.23,1:33:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,it's the eye that you think prevails is\Nyou.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:48.48,1:33:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The eye that you think is you is not the\Nyou. Anything you believe is the you is
Dialogue: 0,1:33:54.71,1:33:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,not the you.\NBecause when the eye that is not you
Dialogue: 0,1:33:59.44,1:34:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,disappears, there is no duality of a\Nspeaker and a subject. There's nothing
Dialogue: 0,1:34:05.28,1:34:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and no one to say that is I. This is\Nthis I am
Dialogue: 0,1:34:11.44,1:34:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,all the things that are quoted\Nin son pious
Dialogue: 0,1:34:16.96,1:34:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,in that infinite silent space. There's\Nnothing to say anything nor is there
Dialogue: 0,1:34:22.32,1:34:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,anything to speak about nor is there any\Nspeaker. There is neither subject nor
Dialogue: 0,1:34:27.44,1:34:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,object.\NEverything then fulfills its
Dialogue: 0,1:34:34.96,1:34:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,potentiality by intention.\Npotentiality becomes actuality. So we
Dialogue: 0,1:34:43.84,1:34:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,start the lecture saying that nothing is\Ncausing anything. If you can make that
Dialogue: 0,1:34:48.32,1:34:54.63,Default,,0,0,0,,jump, you're way ahead of the game\Nalready. Nothing is causing anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:54.63,1:34:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,All that prevails is a consequence of\Nthat which one has become.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:59.92,1:35:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,That which one is\Nthat which you are automatically
Dialogue: 0,1:35:04.80,1:35:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,influences everything and everywhere you\Nwalk. And as you go into a more divine
Dialogue: 0,1:35:09.84,1:35:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,state, you will see as you walk through\Nthe woods, all that's living is aware of
Dialogue: 0,1:35:14.63,1:35:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the divinity of divinity passing them by\Nas a consequence of that which you have
Dialogue: 0,1:35:20.80,1:35:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,become to own your own divinity within.\NSo
Dialogue: 0,1:35:31.12,1:35:36.15,Default,,0,0,0,,you become\Nyour own potential by intention and by
Dialogue: 0,1:35:36.15,1:35:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,agreement.\Nto become
Dialogue: 0,1:35:40.56,1:35:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,that which the infinite potential of\Nwhich you're born to manifest that and
Dialogue: 0,1:35:46.63,1:35:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,without the help of God is not possible.\NSo we know that conquering the ego first
Dialogue: 0,1:35:51.60,1:35:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,of all is frankly impossible.\NNo human being can conquer the ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:58.88,1:36:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't be done.\NThat would be like picking yourself up
Dialogue: 0,1:36:02.63,1:36:06.15,Default,,0,0,0,,by your bootstraps. It is not a\Npossibility
Dialogue: 0,1:36:06.15,1:36:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,for the ego at its level of strength to\Nsurmount the ego. Yeah. No. As a
Dialogue: 0,1:36:11.44,1:36:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,fulcrum, it needs something a higher\Npower.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:15.44,1:36:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing can be done without the help of\Ndivinity.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:19.19,1:36:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It's by the grace of God.\NSo you'll see that the experiencer
Dialogue: 0,1:36:32.23,1:36:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,is yang\Nand you'll see that the self is yin.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:41.67,1:36:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, spiritual awareness arises\Nnot as an acquisition
Dialogue: 0,1:36:46.96,1:36:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but as a surrender to that which stands\Nin its way. Huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:52.00,1:36:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,At the end,\Nthe belief
Dialogue: 0,1:36:56.48,1:37:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that I myself am the source of my own\Nlife.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:04.32,1:37:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The knowingness to surrender it came as\Na surrender. Did not come as an
Dialogue: 0,1:37:08.88,1:37:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,acquisition. If the thought had arisen\Nsince the beginning of time, I was
